<h2>Course Content</h2>

<h3>1. Advanced Referral Strategies</h3>
<p>
This module focuses on scaling your referral efforts beyond basic sharing. Students learn how to strategically position their links, create value-driven content, and build trust with their audience.
</p>

<p>
Instead of spamming links, learners understand how to attract people organically through useful information, consistency, and smart positioning. The goal is to create a system where referrals come naturally through influence and credibility.
</p>

<h3>2. Target Audience & Marketing Basics</h3>
<p>
Success in digital growth depends heavily on understanding your audience. This section teaches how to identify the right group of people based on interests, behavior, and needs.
</p>

<p>
Students learn basic marketing principles such as value proposition, content positioning, and engagement strategies. This helps them create content and campaigns that actually connect with people rather than being ignored.
</p>

<h3>3. Free Tools for Digital Workers</h3>
<p>
Efficiency is key to growth. In this module, students are introduced to a range of free tools that can help with content creation, organization, communication, and analytics.
